hopobject.body: Lost credit card healthinsurancemn.com Not everyone was an admirer. One colleague claimed that Helen Thomas’s aggressive questioning of Ronald Reagan had destroyed the tradition of presidents visiting the press section of Air Force One, while one of Gerald Ford’s press aides accused her of oversimplifying complex issues. On the other hand, there were many who applauded her for pushing presidents to explain their policies.
